The diagnosis of virus in relatively crude extracts of Oryetes larvae and adults could possibly be affected by the presence of varying levels of insect extract so this phenomenon was examined further. Three parallel dilution series of virus were made: one in buffer, one in a constant, high concentration of insect extract and the third, like that illustrated in Fig. 3 (a), was a dilution series in buffer of virus plus insect extract (Fig. 3b). The detection level in the purified virus dilution series is about 3o ng/ml but both curves for virus in insect

